<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="153" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9482</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-03T17:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2392. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 73. French desire inter-Allied committee, Paris, to send joint
                                resolution to S[ociété] S[uisse de] S[urveillance Economique],
                                Berne, that unless necessary steps to include some names of S.S.S.
                                members in Swiss black list are completed before a certain date,
                                Paris committee will compile list and include S.S.S. members engaged
                                in contraband trade giving S.S.S. appeal from decisions. French
                                consider such inclusion will not violate article 3 of S.S.S.
                                agreement. Have telegraphed <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>, Paris, to
                                communicate with you and determine whether you approve this proposed
                                resolution before acting. Telegraph your opinion Washington
                                also.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>